parameters
thirty-three years go by and not once do you come home to find a man sitting in your bedroom that is a man you don't know who came a long way to deliver one very specific message: lock your back door, you idiot however invincible you imagine yourself to be you are wrong thirty-three years go by and you loosen the momentum of teenage nightmares your breasts hang like a woman's and you don't jump at shadows anymore instead you may simply pause to admire those that move with the grace of trees dancing past streetlights and you walk through your house without turning on lamps sure of the angle from door to table from table to staircase sure of the number of steps seven to the landing two to turn right then seven more sure you will stroll serenely on the moving walkway of memory across your bedroom and collapse with a sigh onto your bed shoes falling thunk thunk onto the floor and there will be no strange man suddenly all that time sitting there sitting there on what must be the prize chair in your collection of uncomfortable chairs with a wild look in his eyes and hands that you cannot see holding what? you do not know so sure are you of the endless drumming rhythm of your isolation that you are painfully slow to adjust if only because yours is not that genre of story still and again, life cannot muster the stuff of movies no bullets shattering glass instead fear sits patiently fear almost smiles when you finally see him though you have kept him waiting for thirty-three years and now he has let himself in and he has brought you fistfuls of teenage nightmares though you think you see, in your naivete that he is empty handed and this brings you great relief at the time new as you are, really, to the idea that even after you've long since gotten used to the parameters they can all change while you're out one night having a drink with a friend some big hand may be turning a big dial switching channels on your dreams until you find yourself lost in them and watching your daily life with the sound off and of course having cautiously turned down the flame under your eyes there are more shadows around everything your vision a dim flashlight that you have to shake all the way to the outhouse your solitude elevating itself like the spirit of the dead presiding over your supposed repose not really sleep at all just a sleeping position and a series of suspicious sounds a clanking pipe a creaking branch the footfalls of a cat all of this and maybe the swish of the soft leather of your intruder's coat as you walk him step by step back to the door having talked him down off the ledge of a very bad idea soft leather, big feet, almond eyes the kinds of details the police officer would ask for later with his clipboard and his pistol in your hallway yesterday i was thinking about stereotypes and labels. i was thinking about all the different things i could be stereotyped as over the years and all the different things i wanted others to stereotype me as. and then i was thinking about all the things i'd label myself as and what i wanted to stereotype myself as. thats a hell of a lot of labels for one person. and its weird how even tho everybody "hates" stereotypes, everyone WANTS to be labeled at the same time. everyone wants to fit into a nice neat category, and know exactly who they are at all times, but its just not possible.

well my brother woke me up blasting on his trumpet and he's still going strong, so i can't practice, do homework, or study, and my parents aren't here so I can't leave.  So I figured I'd update. lol.

Um I've been home since last Friday night (when we got towed).  I went to the high school musical last weekend and I can honestly say I was very impressed with how it all came together.  Also it was so great to see everyone.  I couldn't stay after the show b/c I had to work at 5 (it was the sunday show), but I did make-up Saturday and Sunday, so I got to chill w/everyone before the shows.  I was afraid it'd be awkward and people would be like "um get out of here this is our show" haha but they weren't it was so much fun and Kara was there too so i wasn't the only old person haha.  But yeah it was so great to see everyone and they all made me very proud.  

Basically for the rest of this week off I've been working, doing homework & practicing, going to the gym, seeing Jesse (altho I actually haven't seen him that much), and shopping for much-needed supplies (when I go home is when I stock up seeing as I go to school in the middle of nowhere). Fun fun.  Oh well I can't complain its just so nice to be out of Potsdam and the -20 to -30 degree weather.  It's been 30 degrees here all week and I've been in tank tops!


Anyways, last night was super fun.  Lynzie had a bunch of people over.  We all basically just chilled and watched Hitch (bootleg), which I just saw the other day, but I was down w/seeing again cuz it was sort of cute.  Then we decided to have a Mighty Taco party (one of the best ideas I've ever heard of).  It was SO funny.  There were so many of us, and it was after 1 am, so only the drive-thru was open, so we were all standing out in the cold in a huge crowd eating our food and like, dancing a little to stay warm (someones car was blasting music).  And when we were in the drive-thru line, I was like the biggest dumbass ever!!!!  I pulled up to the menu thing and was like "oh let's check out the prices!" and then after I looked at them, I DROVE FORWARD!  Before they could take my order!!!!!!   So then I had to beep my horn so the van behind me would back up and I had to back up and Lori had to order out the back window!!  lmao then go figure it was Janelle at the drive-thru window lmao.  So I totally embarassed myself in front of someone who actually knows me~

But yeah so then we were all chilling and it was like: me, lynz, lori mammoser, ryan rogers, ryan penna, steve schrieber, jamie bermingham, jess staub, lisa altherr, laura, dick, ...crap I don't remember who else.  Katie Gard and her bf were there earlier but the didn't go to Mighty.  But then Eve and Sara Ressing and Eve's bf showed up too which was hysterical!  We had a huge party, and then all these cars started pulling up getting together and it looked like they wanted to join the party, but we were ready to rumble lol.  So after some random guy tried to be cool and do some intense burnout things, we all drove away cuz we figured the cops were coming.  So I went back to Lynzie Rae's to take her home and Lori to her car and we ended up chilling there for a while longer just talking and stuff.  It was cool.  I didn't get home til really late tho and then well, you know the rest, Mark woke me up at 930 and btw I'm all swollen up and disgusting and having like, an allergic reaction or something so thats cute. lol pretty girl. hahaha.  awww i miss my girls on long island!

one of my childhood dreams came true today.  i got to ride in the back of a car that was being towed...it was tilted up and everything!!!

lol yeah jen's car broke down in rochester and there wasn't enough room in the tow truck for all of us so me and brian got to ride in the car.  i don't really think that's legal...but it was sure fun!!!

(well except for the fact that there was no heat.....yeah my fingers and toes were white they were so frozen and we could see our breath in the car)

lol but still it was a fun, adventurous, and exciting experience!  And we spent lots of the car ride listening to Delilah hahahaha  gotta love that woman.
i think sometimes people just say things cuz they think they should and not cuz they necessarily mean them. Ok with that deep thought its time for a 15 minute nap.

oh man its been a few days...um well...Valentines' Day was wonderful, because despite being in arctic Potsdam, Jesse sent me the most beautiful flowers I have ever seen in my life, delivered right to my dorm room.  Seriously, I usually don't even like flowers, but they're breathtaking.  It's an arragement of pink lilies (LILIES ARE MY FAVE FLOWERS EVER), pink baby roses, and babies breath.  You seriously have to see them, you'd melt.  The boy scored some major points this V-day ahha.  And I think he liked my gift of a demonic stuffed kitty with a pretty bow, hershey's kisses, and a hilarious love letter written entirely in conversation hearts, too. hahaha.

OMG AMAZING WEEKEND!!!!!  It was so incredible and I can never, never thank my girls enough.  They took me w/them when they went home to Long Island this past weekend.  It was amazing.  Even the 7 hour drive was absolutely awesome.  I never knew I could have so much fun in a long car ride.  It was my first experience seeing NYC when we drove in Friday night, and it looked amazing, all illuminated.  Then Saturday Chris, Amy's bf (who's a pilot) took me and Amy flying in a small plane over Manhattan.  It was so incredible.  Not to mention it was absolutely gorgeous out and we got some incredible pictures of the sun rising over the water.  It was so awesome, I can't even describe it.  Then we went out to breakfast, and then Amy took me to Port Jeff, this gorgeous little nautical town that is just so ME!  For real.  I instantly fell in love with it.  We even went shopping in a couple of the little gift shops and got some jewelry.  They had some awesome beachy stuff, but there was also an Indian store that had the most incredible jewelry, belts, and purses...I can't wait to go back over Christmas!  Then we went to the beach.  OMG.  It was quite possibly the best beach I have ever seen in my life.  The sand was so fine and perfect, the water was so blue....it was ridiculous.  And the funny thing is that Amy told me that a lot of kids hate to go to that beach b/c its so rocky....but its not rocky at all, there's just amazing shells and smooth stones all over (which I collected some of to decorate my room w/ haha im such a dork!)  But yeah, after that we went out to Panera to meet up w/Cara, Christa, and their friend Katie.  Good times...I friggin love Panera (I've had it in Virginia before...its incredible) I wish we had one in Buffalo.  Then we chilled for a little while before having an incredible dinner that Mama Po (Amy's mom) prepared for us.  They have sit down dinners almost EVERY NIGHT.  I can't even fathom that.  I think we generally only do that on holidays.  And then me, Cara, and Christa went to see Christa's little bro in the high school drama.  He was so cute and funny!  And their school was ridiculous.  There were over 600 ppl in their graduating class, their school is ENORMOUS and shaped like a HAND OF ALL THINGS, and there's trailers all over cuz they're adding on to the school to make it even bigger.  But yeah, after the drama we went out and rented A Goofy Movie (amazing movie!) and Coyote Ugly (also incredible!) ha, but we only got about 10 mins into Coyote Ugly before me and Amy fell asleep, so we all just went to bed lol.  Sunday morning we got up, ran some errands, and made an awesome brunch for everybody's families.  I love all their families by the way...they're awesome.  Oh and all my friends live in friggin ridiculous houses.  I'm so jealous.  They need to teach Barbie a thing or two about interior decorating haha.  After that we hit the dusty trail.  Spirits were not quite as high on the way back due to a number of factors such as getting a speeding ticket and well, I was quite unhappy b/c I kind of lost something that's VERY important...not to mention we all had exams to dread.  Lol I had a piano test today and I have an anthro exam tomorrow morning. augh. lol.  Speaking of which, since I didn't get a whole lot of studying in, I should probably at least get some sleep for that thing lol.

So I'm out.

Thanks again, girls, for an absolutely fantastic weekend!!!  I can't thank you enough!!!

I quit cheerleading...and I'm honestly very relieved that I did.  I also wanna give myself props for admitting for once when something was just too much for me.  Usually I'm a stubborn little asshole and I just suck it up and deal, but then I end up having like, mental breakdowns. ha.  But yeah, with my music major, I just really couldn't handle it.  Cheering here is a HUGE committment, not to mention that its rather embarassing.  Yeah, it is.  It's not like high school at all.  The squad has potential for good mounts, but do you think we can show those off at hockey games?  No, we just sit there and clap our poms and look like retards.  Plus, one of the captains is an extreme bitch and I just really couldn't deal with her.  It's sad, because I *LOVE* cheering, and I love most of the girls on the squad, and I really like the coach and I *love* THE UNIFORMS, and I love the fact that we get all this free shit and it counts as a PE credit...but I really just don't have the time for it.  It's just additional stress that I don't need right now.  Not to mention I have a ton of concerts for Studio that I'm required to go to that completely conflict with practices.  So I quit.  And now I'm free.  Well except for the little matter of Crane owning my soul.  Ha.  Maybe I'll just quit that, too lol.
Roxychic704: "Yesterday is gone. Tomorrow has not yet come. We have only today. Let us begin." ~~Mother Teresa....shes really saying.. "Theresa, quit cheerleading if you want to live"..haha

So apparently I'm a Potsdam Bears Cheerleader...lol

Yeah so I know I'm a total hypocrite cuz I was totally bashing them, and then yesterday one of them came up to me and asked me to try out and I was like "why do u need people that bad? oh ok I guess I will.." lol and here I am, a college cheerleader lol.  Except its not like most college squads where theyre AMAZING and huge and coed and everyone can tumble like whoa and such....nope...this squad currently has like 12 girls on it and a few of them have absolutely no cheering experience whatsoever lol.


But honestly, lately I've been missing cheering so much, so I'm actually kind of excited.  Even though we cheer for um, hockey?  And basketball.  Lol.  That's cute hahaha.  And we have to come back super early from Christmas break which SUCKS.  And I'm worried about being way too busy and stressed w/all my music and stuff, not to mention straining my voice (cuz I kinda need it!!!!).  But I guess I'm just gonna play things by ear and see how things go.  

And to be honest, I've got to admit the squad has SOME potential.  A few of the girls are really good.  The 2 captains, another sophomore, and even a couple of the freshman are def pretty good.  One of the captains, Kim, went to Nationals w/her high school COED team and WON ALL FOUR YEARS!!!  I was like HO-LY SHIT.  Lol.  

But yeah, they thought I was pretty good, I picked up on stuff fast, my motions were really sharp (the insides of my arms hurt already haha), and I actually did pretty well when I was thrown into a couple mounts basing and backing.  So they said I'm gonna be like the wildcard that can do both things, and gets thrown into either whenever they need me.  Sweet.  Hehe they did happen to mention that we will be working on our jumps a lot, so not to worry. hahahahaha yeah I know mine suck ass. lol.  It's all good. 

But yeah so we'll see how this whole college cheering thing goes...I'm kinda excited...even tho it's gonna take up a LOT of my time!

on that note...

...a good title for me I think...well, sometimes. Ok, let's face it, I often do a lot of breaking. But I'm working on it. I'm getting better at dealing. I'm building endurance for when times get rough, you might say. Saturday was THE KENNYS. I did not want to go. At all. I thought it was gonna be SUCH a colossal waste of a Saturday. Boy, was I wrong. I left the house at like 10:30 am to go get Eve and drive her and Molly over to their mom's house so Eve could get her character shoes. Good times! hahah classic car dancing! I'm so glad we're friends again. (There was a very long period during elementary school and jr high where we despised each other...I think it was a competition thing). Anyways, believe it or not, we've matured. :0) Then we went to the Kenny's after a super fun and remeniscent busride. At the Kenny's we warmed up onstage and took a BORING tour of Shea's that including like, no cool spots in the theater. Then we had a looong waiting period where we ate a lot of food, met Meredith Lipke in the elevator illegally, and basically just chatted it up and had a good ol' time. I talked to Lisa and Jesse, and I saw Taylor onstage but I didn't see her to talk to her after. Next the show began, some of the younger girls decided I should give a pep talk. (ha cuz im so good at those!? LOL) It was super retarded but at least everyone actually listened to my ramblings haha. I told them about how when I was three, I saw CATS (my first musical!) at Shea's. I was so excited by the way the actors came right out into the audience and how awesome all the dancing and singing was, and at that moment, I decided that someday I would perform at Sheas. And here we were, about to perfom AT SHEAS. Well I think that's just awesome and congrats on all of us (esp the adults involved) just for making it THAT far!!! Then during the show we did good although my voice was a lil raspy and far back in my throat. Damn. But its ok, cuz everyone else did awesome. All the other schools were really good, though, and we were the underdogs so I definately did NOT think we would win. Not a chance. So each school got called up for its spotlight award. We got stage design. (Yeah Cindy Sweich!!!) Then came the special awards. These awards are individual but they only go to people who do not win the BIG award (kind of to spread out the recognition of talent). No one from Eden won any, although I half expected Ryan to win for leading actor. Then came the big one...yes, the $5000 check, the medals, the shadowbox, the assembly...the whole shebang.... everyone was holding hands and shaking and nervous and I was all "dont be guys, obv we didn't win" and then Lipke announced it.... EDEN JR/SR HIGH SCHOOL!!!! aughhH!!!!! I think we all went crazy for about 3 hours! LITERALLY!!! we were shocked and overjoyed and shocked again. It was awesome. And Erica reminded me that we really and truly have had an incredible year as far as extracurriculars go. We had an AMAZING cheerleading season. We did awesome, and the football team nearly went all the way. It was incredible. And now we've won the Kenny's!! Ok, after a whole bunch of us went out to dinner at Chef's and I got home around quarter after 11. I went to Lynzie's and slept over. In the morning...DASHBOARD. We drove to West Seneca to get the boys and then we drove over to Niagra Dome. When we pulled into the parking lot (at like 1) Maeve was like "HOLY CRAP, THATS THE GET UP KIDS!!!!" Cuz there was a group of guys that looked suspiciously like rock stars standing outside the tour busses. We FREAKED out. We went over there, feeling incredibly creepy and stalkerish, and MET CHRIS CARRABBA AND THE GET UP KIDS!!!!! I got Chris to sign my shirt and I got a picture w/him. They even invited us to gamble w/them haha. And we invited them to come eat hot dogs w/us. LOL. Later we chilled in the parking lot and played lacrosse and frisbee and such. Good times. Then we got in line at like 3 and I complained. A LOT. I was pissy. let's face it, I had had a bad week and was on like, no sleep. while we were waiting in line, we saw mike marsh, so of course we went over and started a convo. (hes the dashboard drummer). But yeah, the concert was so worth it. I got a shirt, and a pick from Say Anything. I had front row. I even got to go BEHIND the barricade for Thrice and like, sit on the stage! Me and Jill were the only ones back there. It was quality. TINY hooked us up hehehe! (a HUGE bodyguard, and yes his name was Tiny) Get Up Kids were AWESOME, even though they only played songs off their new cd, which I dont have. They were still incredible. And Say anything was good too, and Thrice was actually really good even tho they were super hardcore and I got shoved into a speaker haha. and then.....DASHBOARD. amazing. Simply amazing. He played both old and new songs, solo and with the band. and he was SO GOOD. For real. he even MENTIONED US onstage!!!! He was all "This has been one of the best tour locations...etc...It's been so fun...we even got invited to a barbeque earlier!" WOO! lol hehe. The only bad thing about it was that I was right by the exit so all the sick ppl kept having to go by me and they were all gross, and there were these two OBNOXIOUS girls behind me screaming along, so I was really angry. EXCUSE ME BUT I DID NOT PAY TO COME HERE AND HEAR YOU SING!!!! But yeah. Awesome. And we talked to Chris (Carrabba) again after the show. He signed my ticked and we chatted it up (a little!). He really was pretty cool, although I guess he has to be for publicity anyways lol. He's so tiny!!! He's only 5'5" (I'm 5'6") and he's WAY skinnier than me!!! LOL I was like, wow I feel enormous. lol But yeah, terrific evening, thanks guys I had such a blast!!! I didn't get home til like 1 am and I had to go to school this morning but it was all good! I HOPE INCUBUS TURNS OUT THIS AWESOME!!!!!

I have to decide where to go to college by TOMORROW!!!

The choices are down to POTSDAM vs. FREDONIA.

but i honestly DONT KNOW WHICH ONE TO CHOOSE!!!  originally i was leaning Potsdam, but now that I look at it again, I feel like all my reasons for Potsdam are not exactly related to the music program (which would be a rather important thing to consider).

Potsdam:

PROS: its far away, 200 eden kids arent going there, its a good enough school, its giving me more money

CONS: its in the middle of nowhere, its cold

Fredonia:

PROS: Tylock said the voice teachers are better, there's more student organizations, i had an awesome audition there and my judge (who used to be my old voice teachers old voice teacher) had me singing better than ive ever sung before in only a matter of 5 minutes of vocal warm-ups, i'd get better student-teaching opportunities, theres tons of practice rooms

CONS: its more expensive, its right around the corner, i practically grew up there every summer at camp, like 200 eden kids are going there (and about 3 into the music program), i hate dr. lang, the campus isnt as fun.

Yeah, you should probably help me decide, as im pretty pressed for time here!

I got accepted to SYRACUSE in the dual program in the College of Visual and Performing Arts and the School of Education! Wow I def never expected that one! Still though, its mondo expensive, and even tho the campus and location are ideal, potsdam and fredonia are way cheaper and def better music schools...but i dunno....we shall see.... *I love you, Jesse! hehe
